about.summary: GGobi is an open source visualization program for exploring high-dimensional data. It provides highly dynamic and interactive graphics such as tours, as well as familiar graphics such as the scatterplot, barchart and parallel coordinates plots. Plots are interactive and linked with brushing and identification.

name: ggobi
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.2.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: ggobi
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url: http://www.ggobi.org/downloads/ggobi-2.1.11.tar.bz2
  sha256: 2c4ddc3ab71877ba184523e47b0637526e6f3701bd9afb6472e6dfc25646aed7
  patches:
    - osx_patch  # [osx]

build:
  skip: True  # [win]
  number: 1

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - autoconf
    - automake
    - pkg-config
    - make
  host:
    - gtk2
    - libxml2
  run:
    - gtk2
    - libxml2

test:
  commands:
    - test -e $PREFIX/bin/ggobi

about:
  home: http://www.ggobi.org/
  license: BSD_3_clause
  summary: GGobi is an open source visualization program for exploring high-dimensional
    data. It provides highly dynamic and interactive graphics such as tours, as well as
    familiar graphics such as the scatterplot, barchart and parallel coordinates plots.
    Plots are interactive and linked with brushing and identification.
  license_family: BSD

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bgruening
    - dpryan79
